{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"6374e","heading":"Federal fleet conservation requirements","label":"6374e Federal fleet conservation requirements","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch77/schIII/ptH","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective on the date that is 1 day after , see , set out as a note under , The Congress.Dec. 19, 2007section 1601 of Pub. L. 110–140section 1824 of Title 2"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Mandatory reduction in petroleum consumption","label":"a Mandatory reduction in petroleum consumption","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 18 months after , the Secretary shall issue regulations for Federal fleets subject to to require that, beginning in fiscal year 2010, each Federal agency shall reduce petroleum consumption and increase alternative fuel consumption each year by an amount necessary to meet the goals described in paragraph (2).December 19, 2007section 6374 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Goals","label":"2 Goals","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The goals of the requirements under paragraph (1) are that not later than , and for each year thereafter, each Federal agency shall achieve at least a 20 percent reduction in annual petroleum consumption and a 10 percent increase in annual alternative fuel consumption, as calculated from the baseline established by the Secretary for fiscal year 2005.October 1, 2015","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Milestones","label":"3 Milestones","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fa%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"interim numeric milestones to assess annual agency progress towards accomplishing the goals described in that paragraph; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fa%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a requirement that agencies annually report on progress towards meeting each of the milestones and the 2015 goals.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Plan","label":"b Plan","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Requirement","label":"1 Requirement","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The regulations under subsection (a) shall require each Federal agency to develop a plan, and implement the measures specified in the plan by dates specified in the plan, to meet the required petroleum reduction levels and the alternative fuel consumption increases, including the milestones specified by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Inclusions","label":"B Inclusions","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identify the specific measures the agency will use to meet the requirements of subsection (a)(2); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"quantify the reductions in petroleum consumption or increases in alternative fuel consumption projected to be achieved by each measure each year.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Measures","label":"2 Measures","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the use of alternative fuels;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the acquisition of vehicles with higher fuel economy, including hybrid vehicles, neighborhood electric vehicles, electric vehicles, and plug-in hybrid vehicles if the vehicles are commercially available;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the substitution of cars for light trucks;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an increase in vehicle load factors;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F2%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a decrease in vehicle miles traveled;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"F","heading":null,"label":"F","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2/F","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F2%2FF","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a decrease in fleet size; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"G","heading":null,"label":"G","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2/G","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s6374e/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs6374e%2Fb%2F2%2FG","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"other measures.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
